bilingual.source: Her taste in music is unlike mine.
bilingual.target: 她的音乐品味不像我的。

bilingual.source: Unlike his brother, John is very quiet.
bilingual.target: 不像他的兄弟，约翰非常安静。

bilingual.source: Scalars do not have direction, unlike vectors.
bilingual.target: 标量没有方向，不像向量。

bilingual.source: Air is a compressible fluid, unlike water.
bilingual.target: 空气是一种可压缩的流体，不像水那样。

bilingual.source: This painting is unlike any other in the gallery.
bilingual.target: 这幅画不像画廊里的任何其他画作。

bilingual.source: Unlike most people, she enjoys working late at night.
bilingual.target: 不像大多数人，她喜欢在深夜工作。

bilingual.source: Bosons can occupy the same quantum state, unlike fermions.
bilingual.target: 玻色子可以占据相同的量子态，不像费米子。

bilingual.source: The weather today is unlike anything we've seen this season.
bilingual.target: 今天的天气不像我们这个季节见过的任何天气。

bilingual.source: She always keeps her room clean, unlike her sluttish roommate.
bilingual.target: 她总是保持房间干净，不像她那个邋遢的室友。

bilingual.source: Solids have a definite shape and volume, unlike liquids and gases.
bilingual.target: 固体具有确定的形状和体积，不像液体和气体。

yingyinNormal.en: Unlike Las Vegas, L.A. doesn't have roads smart enough to move all this traffic. And unlike Dallas, there's no room here to build new freeways.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不像拉斯维加斯，洛杉矶的道路是不够智能的，也不像达拉斯,没有足够空间造高速公路。

yingyinNormal.en: Unlike my mole, which is holding steady at the size of a navy bean.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不像我的痣，一直都跟菜豆那么大。

yingyinNormal.en: And what about Harold Finch and his associates? That's unlike you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那哈罗德·芬奇和他的帮手呢？这可真不像你。

yingyinNormal.en: But there's good news. Unlike the dinosaurs, we can leave Earth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是有好消息，不像恐龙那样，我们可以离开地球。

yingyinNormal.en: She was loyal. And careful. All of this feels extremely unlike her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她的确很忠诚，小心谨慎，这些都不像她会做的事。

yingyinNormal.en: Unlike this house, the library will be completely quiet, so I can focus on my roommate selection.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不像我们家，图书馆会非常安静，我就可以专心选室友了。

yingyinNormal.en: I understand that, unlike Leonard, they're at the top of their respective fields. Boy, you suck.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我了解到，不像莱纳德，他们都是各自领域的权威人物。你个烂人。

yingyinNormal.en: See, I've been waiting my whole life to be engaged, and unlike some people, I'm only planning on doing this once.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我花了一辈子等着订婚，不像某些人，我只计划做一次。

yingyinNormal.en: Which side do you come down on? I'll let you know after tonight. Unlike some people, I'm going in with an open mind.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你支持哪一种轨距呢？今晚过后我会让你知道，不像某些人，起码我会带着开放的态度去听。

yingyinNormal.en: All that proves is that I'm honest, unlike a president who would use the Department of Justice to target his political opponent for his own personal gain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这只能证明我的诚实，不像总统那样为了个人利益，利用司法部去攻击他的对手。

yingyinNormal.en: I tried to bench you. You refused. Unlike everyone else in your life, I don't work for you. And due to that fact, we're now in a flying doughnut billions of miles from Earth with no backup. I'm backup. No, you're a stowaway.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我让你别插手的。你不肯。不像你人生中的其他所有人，我不为你工作。因为这个，我们现在在一艘飞行甜甜圈上离地球十万八千里还没有后援。我是后援。不，你是偷渡的。

yingyinNormal.en: A living weapon unlike anything we've ever seen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个不同于我们所见过的活武器。

yingyinNormal.en: Hiding from people who needed my help. Unlike you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 躲开那些需要援助的人 你就不一样

yingyinNormal.en: Not unlike the Foot Clan and what they'd like to do to our city.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就像大脚帮对我们城市的所作所为。

yingyinNormal.en: Not me, but, yes, someone did. Not unlike butchering a herd of cattle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不是我，但是，是的，有人在做。就像在屠宰场里宰畜生。

yingyinNormal.en: You are extraordinary, my sons, unlike anything the world has ever seen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 孩子们，你们是非比寻常的，是世间绝无仅有的。

yingyinNormal.en: I need the one person who, unlike me, learned to see through your bullshit long ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我需要那个，和我不一样，早就能看穿你鬼话的人。

yingyinNormal.en: Unlike the nicely embellished fictions on your blog, John, real life is rarely so neat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 和你博客上那些精妙小说不一样，约翰，真实的世界从没那么明了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well Raj, I just want to say that I'd never betray your trust. Unlike Leonard I respect you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个，拉杰，我只是想说，我绝不会背叛你，不会像莱纳德那样，我尊重你。

yingyinNormal.en: But unlike Edison, we've got some very impressive technology these days to help with the search.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但和爱迪生不同的是，如今我们有了很专业的技术以帮助寻找能源。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: But <highlight>unlike</highlight> in friendships, you need coworkers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但与友谊不同的是，你需要同事。

examination_example.sentence: The H-2A visa has no numerical cap, <highlight>unlike</highlight> the H-2B visa for nonagricultural work, which is limited to 66,000 a year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与非农业工作的H-2B签证不同，H-2A签证没有数字上限，后者的上限为每年6.6万份。

examination_example.sentence: But, <highlight>unlike</highlight> with mining claims, the community takes control of what happens next.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是，与采矿业不同的是，社区将控制接下来发生的事情。
